OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA dry day. Rather cloudy at
OL,6,Ffirst in parts of the west but
OL,7,Fgenerally broken cloud allowing
OL,8,Fincreasing spells of sunshine as the
OL,9,Fday goes on. Becoming very warm, even
OL,10,Fhot inland, but a tempering breeze on
OL,11,Fthe east coast.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FA dry evening with some
OL,14,Fsunshine. The night will then stay dry
OL,15,Fwith long clear periods, perhaps the
OL,16,Fodd mist or fog patch around dawn.
OL,17,
OL,18,CThursday:FIt will be another fine dry
OL,19,Fday with plenty of sunshine though
OL,20,Fhigh cloud may turn hazy later. Very
OL,21,Fwarm with some cooling sea breezes.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
